The paper deals with the transmission of packets over erasure channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of random linear combinations is a technique commonly used in distributed storage systems (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.IT). The study of delay and its properties is a topic in queuing theory (cs.SI) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
